<!-- 08 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Samsung jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Samsung service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung RF23M French Door, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice bucket frozen in place; dispenser producing slush instead of cubes. Customer reported the issue had been intermittent for 3 months and had just become continuous.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Ice maker assembly failure consistent with the well-documented RF-series Twin Cooling pattern. Bucket reset possible but ice crystals on bucket exterior and audible fan grind from the ice compartment indicated the assembly itself had failed, not just a thaw cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Full ice maker assembly replacement with OEM Samsung part (in stock at regional distribution, 1-day lead). Bucket reseal, dispenser fan inspection, controller reset.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $485 total. Two visits over 24 hours (diagnostic, then repair after part arrived).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung WF45R front-load washer, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Loud grinding during spin cycles, progressively worse over the past month. Customer asked if it was a belt issue.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Drum bearing failure, confirmed by manual rotation test (audible roughness, lateral play in drum), stethoscope check on the rear seal area, and visual inspection through the access panel. Manufacture date 2021, so just past 4 years, pattern-typical timing for the WF bearing issue.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair recommendation:</strong> Quoted both paths honestly. Repair (full tub assembly + labor): $1,180. Replacement: customer's choice, comparable WF45 around $1,000-$1,200. Customer chose repair given the matching DV dryer was still working well.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $1,180 total. Two visits over 5 days (parts lead time on tub assembly).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Samsung NX58R gas range, Newport Beach</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Center burner not igniting; spark module clicking but no flame. Other four burners working normally.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Spark igniter on the affected burner ohms-out tested fine. Burner port partially clogged with cooking debris. Spark module functional (other burners igniting), so issue isolated to that burner's port and orifice.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Burner cap and grate cleaning, port and orifice clearing with brush and air, spark electrode reseating. Verified ignition on first turn for all five burners.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $145 total. Same-day, completed in 50 minutes on the diagnostic visit.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

